byline.contributor: Sophia Kishkovsky reported from Moscow, and Alison Smale from Berlin.
byline.original: By SOPHIA KISHKOVSKY and ALISON SMALE

abstract: Crimean Tatars protesting Russia's annexation of peninsula continue blocking food deliveries from Ukraine; German officials, concerned for future of tenuous cease-fire, urge caution and warn against planned elections in Crimea.
lead_paragraph: A Tatar leader said no trucks had been allowed in since Sunday, and Germany warned Russia to avert elections planned by separatists.

headline.main: Tatars, Foes of Russia in Crimea, Block Shipments of Food
headline.print_headline: Foes of Russia in Crimea Block Shipments of Food
